From 4bcaf7af462f33416f8c3de3e81b0f48dcf9cb2d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keegan Freyhof <keegan.freyhof@broadcom.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 19:09:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net/bnxt: Change to stats reporting

When polling for stats at a high frequency using
STAT_CTX_QUERY and with substantial traffic, the
HWRM will occasionally include a flipped bit.
This behavior is observed with both heavy RX and
TX traffic.

Fixed this by integrating the masks as reported
by hardware and by adding a filter for hardware
responses that are powers of 2.

RelnoteHeadline: Change to stats reporting

RelnoteDescChg: Integrated masks as reported
by hardware and added a filter for hardware
responses that are powers of 2.

RelnoteIssueDesc: When polling for stats at a
high frequency using STAT_CTX_QUERY and with
substantial traffic, the HWRM will occasionally
include a flipped bit. This behavior is observed
with both heavy RX and TX traffic.

RelnoteVisibility: Default

